From 4f34dcf87e45a450ae34cbe5a68c742a3dcaeea6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: DLM3 Fix <fix@dlm3.app>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 09:07:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: cases page crash, invoice save failure, doctor case
 visibility/notifications
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

BUG 1 — Cases tab crash (lab/admin):
- app/(lab)/cases/page.tsx: wrap tenant resolution and data fetch in
  try/catch with safe fallback defaults (items=[], doctors=[]); render
  friendly error card instead of crashing. Added force-dynamic to avoid
  stale cached renders.
- app/(lab)/cases/error.tsx: new error boundary with retry button
- app/(lab)/billing/page.tsx, app/(lab)/billing/new/page.tsx: same
  try/catch pattern applied (shared root cause: unguarded
  getTenantFromRequest()/Prisma calls)
- app/(lab)/billing/error.tsx: new error boundary
- app/(doctor)/layout.tsx: guard getTenantFromRequest(), redirect to
  /login on failure instead of crashing the whole doctor portal

BUG 2 — Billing invoice can't be saved:
- components/billing/invoice-form.tsx: add client-side validation
  (doctor selected, line item descriptions, qty/price bounds) plus a
  visible error banner. The previous code called server actions inside
  startTransition with no error handling, so validation failures or DB
  errors silently did nothing.
- app/actions/invoices.ts: wrap prisma.invoice.create in try/catch to
  return a clear error instead of throwing on FK/constraint violations

BUG 3 — Doctor-submitted cases invisible to lab/staff + no notification:
- app/actions/cases.ts: doctorSubmitCaseAction now calls notifyLabTeam()
  so all ADMIN/LAB_STAFF users get a CASE_SUBMITTED notification, and
  revalidates /cases, /dashboard, /staff (previously only revalidated
  /doctor/portal, so the lab's cases list and dashboard stayed stale
  until an unrelated rebuild/redeploy refreshed the cache)
- components/shared/notification-bell.tsx: add icon mapping for the new
  CASE_SUBMITTED notification type
